originalText.text: Alex was a great guide! Very passionate about New York, its history, sites, and filming locations! He even added a few minutes to show us inside Central Park.

originalText.text:
I was scammed and given a hybrid bike and being told it is electric.

I had reserved an aluminum bike the night before and was told my bike was not available before this happened. I requested for at least the difference in amount paid and was denied. I cannot in good faith recommended such shady practitioners to anyone and would suggest people looking for bike rentals to go elsewhere.

EDIT: Thanks, I emailed support and at least seems like I'll get my difference refunded.

originalText.text: I went on the 2 hr Harlem tour guided by Richard. He was knowledgeable, kind and sweetest (I forgot to pay gratuity at the end, I am so sorry if you read this). It felt like I was going around with next door David Letterman. Loved learning about the historical spots. The pace was leisurely and easy to follow and the bike was good.

originalText.text: The tandem bike was so crappy from the very beginning. We ended up with a broken chain in the middle of Central Park and had to walk the bike back. The cashier was rude and unhelpful, wanted to charge us $40 for something was not our fault. He kept saying I cannot do anything and it is store policy with an ignoring manner. After talking for 20 min, he gave up and did not charge us. He claimed he has thousands of reviews and our review would not make any difference. He also claimed he had been running the store for 10 years, which I cannot believe as he looked at most 35 and did not care at all about the customers.

originalText.text: Great tour of the city (3 hour) and great guide.   Check-in was easy, but the staff was not super friendly.    Several of the bikes had issues at the start and during the ride.  Double check your bike before you leave.  Overall, great way to see the city.
